# Tests required for behavior changes

When you add or change runtime behavior under `src/`:

1. Add or update automated tests in the same change.
2. Run `npm run test:run` before considering the work done.
3. Prefer unit tests for `src/utils/**` and `src/storage/**` (use `fake-indexeddb` for IndexedDB).
4. Use React Testing Library for components; extend `src/test/fixtures.ts` for shared mocks.
5. Mock `URL.createObjectURL` / `revokeObjectURL` when testing photo UI if needed.
6. Avoid tests that only assert CSS class names or other implementation details without user-visible behavior.

If a change is docs-only or comment-only, tests are not required.
